quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,139,"So they belied him, and We destroyed them. Verily in this is indeed a sign, yet most of them are not believers."
  26,140,"And verily your Lord, He is indeed the All-Mighty, the Most Merciful."
  26,141,"Thamûd (people) belied the Messengers."
  28,85,"Verily, He Who has given you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) the Qur’an (i.e. ordered you to act on its laws and to preach it to others) will surely bring you back to Ma‘âd (place of return, either to Makkah or to Paradise after your death). Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  28,86,"And you were not expecting that the Book (this Qur’ân) would be sent down to you, but it is a mercy from your Lord. So never be a supporter of the disbelievers."
  28,87,"And let them not turn you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) away from (preaching) the Ayât (revelations and verses) of Allâh after they have been sent down to you: and invite (men) to (believe in) your Lord{1} and be not of Al-Mushrikûn (those who associate partners with Allâh, e.g. polytheists, pagans, idolaters, and those who disbelieve in the Oneness of Allâh and deny the Prophethood of Messenger Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم).",footnotes:1:[{28:87} i.e: in the Oneness (Tauhîd ) of Allâh - (1) Oneness of the Lordship of Allâh; (2) Oneness of the worship of Allâh; (3) Oneness of the Names and Qualities of Allâh.]
  29,52,"Say (to them O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  29,53,"And they ask you to hasten on the torment (for them): and had it not been for a term appointed, the torment would certainly have come to them. And surely, it will come upon them suddenly while they perceive not!"
  29,54,"They ask you to hasten on the torment. And verily, Hell, of a surety, will encompass the disbelievers."
  30,31,"(And remain always) turning in repentance to Him (only), and be afraid and dutiful to Him; and perform As-Salât (Iqâmat-as-Salât) and be not of Al-Mushrikûn (the polytheists, idolaters, disbelievers in the Oneness of Allah)."
  30,32,"Of those who split up their religion (i.e. who left the true Islâmic Monotheism), and became sects, [i.e. they invented new things in the religion (Bid‘ah ), and followed their vain desires], each sect rejoicing in that which is with it.{1}",footnotes:1:[{30:32} See the footnote of {3:103}.]
  30,33,"And when harm touches men, they cry sincerely only to their Lord (Allâh), turning to Him in repentance; but when He gives them a taste of His Mercy, behold, a party of them associates partners in worship with their Lord."
  31,16,""
  31,17,""
  31,18,"",footnotes:1:[{31:18}: See the footnote of {22:9}.]
  32,1,"Alif-Lâm-Mîm."
  32,2,"The revelation of the Book (this Qur’ân) in which there is no doubt is from the Lord of the ‘Âlamîn (mankind, jinn and all that exists)!"
  32,3,"Or say they: "